The paper deals with named entity recognition (NER) in short social media posts with accompanying images, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related areas. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which covers image analysis and recognition. The third likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which covers text and multimedia retrieval. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), which covers multimedia analysis and processing. The fifth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which covers social media analysis and modeling.
